WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devinit is unnecessary
#66: FILE: drivers/input/serio/ct82c710.c:178:
+static int __devinit ct82c710_probe(struct platform_device *dev)

CHECK:ALLOC_SIZEOF_STRUCT: Prefer kzalloc(sizeof(*ct82c710_port)...) over kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio)...)
#69: FILE: drivers/input/serio/ct82c710.c:180:
+	ct82c710_port = kzalloc(sizeof(struct serio), GFP_KERNEL);

The allocation style is bad.  In general for family of
allocation functions using sizeof() to get memory size,
constructs like::

  p = alloc(sizeof(struct foo), ...)

should be::

  p = alloc(sizeof(*p), ...)

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#allocating-memory

WARNING:STRLCPY: Prefer strscpy over strlcpy - see: https://lore.kernel.org/r/CAHk-=wgfRnXz0W3D37d01q3JFkr_i_uTL=V6A6G1oUZcprmknw@mail.gmail.com/
#89: FILE: drivers/input/serio/ct82c710.c:189:
+	strlcpy(ct82c710_port->name, "C&T 82c710 mouse port",

WARNING:HOTPLUG_SECTION: Using __devexit is unnecessary
#101: FILE: drivers/input/serio/ct82c710.c:199:
+static int __devexit ct82c710_remove(struct platform_device *dev)

CHECK:LINE_SPACING: Please don't use multiple blank lines
#125: FILE: drivers/input/serio/ct82c710.c:215:
 
+

Vertical space is wasted given the limited number of lines an
editor window can display when multiple blank lines are used.

See: https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html#spaces

